This is Perl module Groonga::QueryBuilder.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - Groonga::QueryBuilder

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
Groonga::QueryBuilder:

    $ cpanm Groonga::QueryBuilder

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf Groonga-QueryBuilder-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd Groonga-QueryBuilder-$version
    $ perl Makefile.PL
    $ make && make test

Then install it:

    $ make install

DOCUMENTATION

Groonga::QueryBuilder documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc Groonga::QueryBuilder

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

